  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/662ef3c2-765b-48e9-89a1-84b6a49fe1a2/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "5be45915418dd33f",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "SENIOR OPERATIONS MANAGER, RIDER PERFORMANCE (MIDDLE EAST)\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drive everything we do. Our Operations team is the heart of Deliveroo—ensuring our three-sided marketplace runs safely, fairly, and efficiently. From designing robust policies to navigating complex regulatory landscapes and scaling global frameworks, we solve high-stakes challenges that protect our community. If you thrive in fast-paced environments, possess strong operational grit, and want to build trust in a global brand—this is the team for you.\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Operations Manager, Rider Performance to join our Middle East team. Reporting to the Director of Operations (Middle East), you will be responsible for building the frameworks and systems that ensure our rider network in the UAE, Kuwait, and Qatar operates at an elite level while helping riders optimise their earnings.\n\nGet to know our Operations https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/operations/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the Middle East Rider Operations team. Operating in a hyper-growth environment, you will solve complex logistics problems by leveraging data to ensure we always have the best-performing riders on the road.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Framework Development: Build effective, scalable, and efficient systems to centralise and manage rider performance across three distinct Middle Eastern markets.\n\n - Strategic Resource Allocation: Design and recommend incentive strategies and resource plans to tackle specific performance gaps or network health issues.\n\n - Performance Tracking: Monitor key metrics and \"unusual\" data trends, conducting deep-dives to uncover root causes and preserve the health of the logistics network.\n\n - Budget Management: Work closely with the wider Rider Ops team to ensure performance initiatives and incentive structures operate within defined budgets.\n\n - Stakeholder Reporting: Provide regular, concise, and high-impact updates on rider performance to senior leadership and global HQ teams.\n\n - Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner with HQ Ops, Product, and Tech to implement new features or tools that improve the experience for riders, restaurants, and customers.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nOur ideal candidate will bring strong expertise in some of these areas and curiosity to grow in others:\n\n - Analytical Mastery: 6+ years of experience in data analytics, consulting, or engineering. You are highly comfortable with large datasets and proficient in SQL and Python.\n\n - Problem-Solving Grit: A proven track record of solving tough, complex problems in a high-growth startup or similar fast-paced environment.\n\n - Ownership Mindset: You take full responsibility for your area, demonstrating the curiosity to diagnose unusual outcomes and the drive to fix them.\n\n - Process Engineering: Experience building scalable tools and structured change methodologies; you enjoy working in and refining process-driven environments.\n\n - Communication \u0026 Influence: Excellent stakeholder management skills, with the ability to translate complex data into clear strategic recommendations.\n\n - Agility: Comfortable handling multiple high-priority workstreams simultaneously, both individually and as part of a regional team.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day\n\nYour work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment\n\nWork close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role\n\nStretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture\n\nCollaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
